illion our investments provide a compelling mix of cost of capital and flexibility to support growth companies we offer a variety of debt structures and equity coinvestments that can be modified over time to adapt to changing business realities our specialties range from senior secured to junior lien to equity and typically include extended interestonly periods flexible amortization schedules and delayed draw capabilities with maturities between three to five years importantly we bring the same level of attention enthusiasm and creativity to every transaction—no matter the size our investment criteria while each of our portfolio companies has its own unique needs the majority of our clients share some common characteristics growth companies primarily in the technology sector mid to latestage growth companies with strong customer validation runrate revenues of  million or greater with good top line growth and revenue visibility a proven management team with a clear vision for success the ability to reasonably project forecasted product andor service demand support from a seasoned venture capital firm or growthfocused private equity sponsor a realistic path to breakeven cash flow within  months of our investment   our team jeffrey bedehead of orix growth capitalwilliam bishopmanaging directorharuyasu yamadavice president joel graggmanaging directordavid orlandellamanaging directorjeff sokolowskidirectorjon weitzeldirectorstasia carsonassociate directorrubens ferozassociate directorlaura johnsonassociate directorgeorge thompsonassociate directorjosh seamanassociate harry wongassociatedeborah blakeadministrative assistant growth capital newsroom orix growth capital invests in venafi jul   orix growth capital announced today that it has completed an investment in venafi inc the industry pioneer and leading provider of machine identity read more orix growth capital invests in revolution foods jun   orix growth capital “orix” and bridge bank today announced that the firms 